                <head>231. Summary of Conclusions of a Mini-Special Coordination Committee
                        Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d231fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                        National Security Council, Institutional Files, Box 119, SCM 059, 3/24/79,
                        Mini <gloss target="#t_SCC_1">SCC</gloss>, Security Assistance for Egypt and
                        Israel. Confidential. The meeting took place in the White House Situation
                        Room. The summary was found attached to a March 26 covering memorandum from
                            <persName corresp="#p_DLG_1">Denend</persName> to <persName
                            corresp="#p_ADL_1">Aaron</persName>, upon which <persName
                            corresp="#p_ADL_1">Aaron</persName> initialed his approval of the
                        summary and added the handwritten notation, “Circulate!” (Ibid.) <persName
                            corresp="#p_DC_1">Dodson</persName> forwarded the summary and <persName
                            corresp="#p_DLG_1">Denend</persName>’s covering memorandum to <persName
                            corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BH_2"
                            >Brown</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MJT_1">McIntyre</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_SGM_1">Seignious</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_JDC_1">Jones</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_TS_1"
                            >Turner</persName> under a separate covering memorandum dated April 2.
                        (Ibid.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1979-03-24T10:04:00-05:00" to="1979-03-24T10:52:00-05:00">March
                            24, 1979, 10:04–10:52 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
